                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/6288.</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mexico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-02-20T21:00:00-06:36">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 20, 1913—9 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>21. The text of the resignation of the President and Vice President is as
                    follows: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p rend="flushleft">
                            <hi rend="italic">The Secretaries of the Chamber of Deputies:</hi>
                        </p>
                        <p>In view of the events which, have occurred since yesterday in the nation
                            and for its greater tranquility we formally resign our posts of
                            President and Vice President, respectively, to which we were elected. We
                            protest whatever may be necessary.</p>
                        <p>Mexico, February 19, 1913.</p>
                        <p rend="right">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Francisco I. Madero.</hi>
                        </p>
                        <p rend="right">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">José M. Pino Suárez</hi>.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
